Detailed Description

A Stream way to read primitive data.

All read requests made by calling methods in this class are directly forwarded to the equivalent function of the underlying operating system.

The following example demonstrates how to use this BufferedOutputStream class.

 MyPage::onInit(Persistence* const savedInstanceState) {
     gaia::base::String filename("output.txt");
     gaia::base::String output("Gaia Code - Examples");

     gaia::storage::FileOutputStream *fos = new gaia::storage::FileOutputStream(*filename);
     gaia::storage::BufferedOutputStream *bos = new gaia::storage::BufferedOutputStream(*fos);

     bos->write(output.getBytes());

     bos->flush();
     bos->close();
 }

void gaia::storage::BufferedOutputStream::write ( const base::ByteArray &  buffer,
int32_t  offset,
int32_t  length 
) [virtual]

Writes length bytes from the byte array buffer starting at offset to this stream.

If there is room in the buffer to hold the bytes, they are copied in. If not, the buffered bytes plus the bytes in buffer are written to the target stream, the target is flushed, and the buffer is cleared.

Parameters:
bufferthe buffer to be written.
offsetthe start position in buffer from where to get bytes.
lengththe number of bytes from buffer to write to this stream.

Reimplemented from gaia::storage::OutputStream.

void gaia::storage::BufferedOutputStream::write ( int32_t  oneByte) [virtual]

Writes one byte to this stream.

Only the low order byte of the integer oneByte is written. If there is room in the buffer, the byte is copied into the buffer and the count incremented. Otherwise, the buffer plus oneByte are written to the target stream, the target is flushed, and the buffer is reset.

Parameters:
oneBytethe byte to be written.
